    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wells bored into a confined aquifer which overflow the wellhead, because the water level of the aquifer lies above the level of the wellhead; the water rises under its own pressure through the borehole.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
